South Africa has recorded 2 073 new coronavirus infections in the last 24-hour cycle, taking the total number to 1 588 221. The country has also recorded 46 new COVID-19 related fatalities on Wednesday. This brings the total number of deaths to 54 557. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in Gauteng. “Regrettably, we report 46 more COVID-19 related deaths: Eastern Cape 4, Free State 1, Gauteng 19, Kwa-Zulu Natal 2, Limpopo 18, Mpumalanga 0, North West 0, Northern Cape 2 and Western Cape 0,” says Dr Mkhize. Recoveries stand at 1 510 385. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 10 739 813. The number of healthcare workers vaccinated under the Sisonke Protocol to date is 353 181. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 588 221 the total number of deaths is 54 557 the total number of recoveries is 1 510 385 and the total number of vaccines administered is 353 181. pic.twitter.com/6DoQbdZGAv — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) May 5, 2021 